lillycoder (0.1.8-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Slash commands collapsed under one /persona namespace. /persona,
    /persona list, /persona show <name>, /persona load <name>,
    /persona add, /persona copy, /persona remove, /persona diff,
    /persona active, /persona evolve. The legacy commands
    (/personas, /setpersona, /personalities, /persona-active,
    /persona-copy, /persona-evolve) all still work and route through
    the new namespace, with a one-shot deprecation tip the first time
    each is used in a session.
  * /persona list now shows the first non-empty line of every
    persona, truncated to 70 chars, so you can tell what each one
    sounds like without loading it. Origin tags (bundled vs user)
    and the (current) marker are kept.
  * Reasoning models that emit OpenAI Harmony channel markers
    (<|channel|>thought<|message|>...<|end|>) used in some recent
    gemma/qwen3-MoE/deepseek-r1 builds are now parsed correctly.
    Channel control tokens are stripped from the visible stream
    instead of leaking; non-final/non-response channels are routed
    as thoughts (hidden unless /thoughts on).
  * Thought segments now render in italic dim grey instead of plain
    dim, so when /thoughts on is enabled they are visually distinct
    from real assistant content.
  * Tool registry unchanged: the model-facing tool names
    (set_persona, list_personas, add_persona, clone_persona,
    set_active_persona, set_evolve, plus the file/shell tools)
    keep working exactly as before. Verified end-to-end against a
    real LLM endpoint.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Thu, 07 May 2026 05:00:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.7-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Six bundled personas instead of one: default (kid coder), tsundere,
    yandere, sweet, adult, analytical. All written in first person with
    explicit anti-roleplay rules so local models stop narrating Lilly
    in the third person or emitting asterisk-actions.
  * /personalities group of slash commands: list, show, load, add,
    remove, diff. Bundled-shadow protection: when a user file overrides
    a bundled persona, lillycoder snapshots the bundled text alongside
    so /personalities diff can later show drift between your fork and
    the upstream version.
  * /persona-active shows which persona is loaded right now, with
    origin (bundled vs user) and on-disk path, plus a warning when the
    in-memory text has diverged from the file.
  * /persona-copy <src> <dst> clones any persona (bundled or user)
    into a new user-owned name. First step of forking for edit.
  * /persona-evolve on now snapshots the current in-memory persona to
    disk and switches the active label to that file, so whatever shape
    Lilly currently has is what evolves. Combined with [ui] last_persona
    persistence, the evolved persona is sticky across launches; bare
    `lillycoder` (no --persona) reloads the last active one.
  * /max-tokens [auto|<n>] and --max-tokens flag. Per-reply token cap,
    persisted to config. 'auto' is now a computed value (about 85% of
    remaining context, capped at 4096), not just an omitted field, so
    reasoning models stop producing empty replies because the server's
    tiny default (llama.cpp's --n-predict defaults to 128) is no longer
    in charge.
  * Five new tools so Lilly manages personas via tool calls instead of
    write_file: list_personas, add_persona, clone_persona,
    set_active_persona, set_evolve. Asking her to "make a pirate
    persona and switch to it" works end to end through the tool
    registry.
  * REPL: live spinner during long tool execution, magenta confirmation
    line when a persona is rewritten, tighter bottom toolbar so it
    stops being dropped on narrow terminals.
  * Removed dead _stream_reply path and its unused imports.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 21:30:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.6-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * REPL: status bar moved to a live bottom toolbar that redraws while
    you type. Shows model, server, ctx fill, current persona, tool
    count, and active flags (thoughts, no-autocompact, evolve,
    bypass-perms). Top welcome line is now a single one-liner so chat
    starts cleaner.
  * New tool set_persona lets the model rewrite its own system prompt
    when the user asks. Permission-gated like any other mutating tool.
  * /persona-evolve [on|off] (and --persona-evolve flag) controls
    whether set_persona persists the new persona to disk under
    ~/.config/lillycoder/personas/. Off by default, in which case the
    new persona only applies for the current session.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 19:30:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.5-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * REPL: /autocompact [on|off] toggles automatic context compaction.
    State is persisted in config.toml under [ui].autocompact. When off
    and context goes past 90 percent, lillycoder warns instead of
    compacting silently.
  * CLI: --no-autocompact disables auto-compaction for the current
    session (overrides the persisted setting).

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 19:00:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.4-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * REPL: end every assistant turn on a fresh line so the prompt no
    longer runs into lilly's last token.
  * Agent: announce each tool call before dispatch ("⏳ name(args)")
    instead of only logging the result, so long-running write/bash
    calls no longer look hung.
  * Reasoning tokens: render <think>...</think> segments and the
    OpenAI-style delta.reasoning_content field as dim grey output.
    Hidden by default; toggle with /thoughts (also accepts on/off),
    persisted in config.toml under [ui].
  * Ctrl+C now interrupts the current turn and returns to the prompt
    instead of crashing out with a traceback. Two Ctrl+Cs within 2
    seconds exit the session (Ctrl+D still exits immediately).
  * Permission prompt: stop swallowing the option keys to Rich markup.
    "[y]es / [n]o / [a]lways / [p]ath" now reads as "(y)es / (n)o /
    (a)lways / (p)ath", and the call summary is printed without
    markup parsing so paths/content with brackets render correctly.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 18:30:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Context window is now read from the server instead of hardcoded to
    8192. Uses /v1/models meta (n_ctx, n_ctx_train) and falls back to
    llama.cpp /props for the runtime n_ctx. Also accepts top-level
    context_length / max_context_length / context_window keys.
  * Banner now shows the active context size and whether it came from
    the server or the 8k fallback.

